etymologies: late 17th century: from French frisquette, from Provençal frisqueto, from Spanish frasqueta

definitions: a thin metal frame keeping the paper in position during printing on a hand press.
shortDefinitions: thin metal frame keeping paper in position during printing on hand press

definitions: fluid or adhesive paper used in painting or crafts to cover areas of a surface on which paint is not wanted

examples.text: over these zones of color, she applies frisket

shortDefinitions: fluid or adhesive paper used in painting
